  "prompt": "What are the best romantic comedy movies?",
  "response": "Romantic comedies have been a beloved genre for decades, offering a mix of humor, love, and heartwarming moments. Here\u2019s a list of some of the best romantic comedy movies, spanning classic and modern films:\n\n### **Classic Romantic Comedies**\n1. **When Harry Met Sally (1989)** - A timeless exploration of friendship, love, and the age-old question: Can men and women just be friends?\n2. **Pretty Woman (1990)** - A modern Cinderella story starring Julia Roberts and Richard Gere.\n3. **Sleepless in Seattle (1993)** - A heartfelt tale of fate and love, starring Tom Hanks and Meg Ryan.\n4. **You've Got Mail (1998)** - Another Tom Hanks and Meg Ryan pairing, blending romance with the early days of the internet.\n5. **Notting Hill (1999)** - A charming story of a bookseller and a Hollywood star, played by Hugh Grant and Julia Roberts.\n\n### **Modern Romantic Comedies**\n1. **Crazy, Stupid, Love (2011)** - A multi-layered romantic comedy with an ensemble cast, including Steve Carell, Ryan Gosling, and Emma Stone.\n2. **The Proposal (2009)** - Sandra Bullock and Ryan Reynolds star in this hilarious fake-marriage tale.\n3. **Love Actually (2003)** - A holiday classic with interconnected love stories featuring an all-star cast.\n4. **To All the Boys I've Loved Before (2018)** - A Netflix original based on the YA novel, delivering sweet, modern romance.\n5. **The Big Sick (2017)** - A heartfelt and funny true story about love, culture, and family.\n\n### **Quirky and Unique Romantic Comedies**\n1. **Silver Linings Playbook (2012)** - A mix of romance, comedy, and drama starring Bradley Cooper and Jennifer Lawrence.\n2. **500 Days of Summer (2009)** - A non-traditional romantic comedy that explores the ups and downs of a relationship.\n3. **Am\u00e9lie (2001)** - A whimsical French film about a shy woman who helps others while navigating her own love life.\n4. **Eternal Sunshine of the Spotless Mind (2004)** - A surreal and deeply emotional story about love and memory, starring Jim Carrey and Kate Winslet.\n5. **The Half of It (2020)** - A modern take on Cyrano de Bergerac, exploring friendship and love in a small town.\n\n### **Cult Favorites**\n1. **10 Things I Hate About You (1999)** - A Shakespearean-inspired teen rom-com with Heath Ledger and Julia Stiles.\n2. **Bridget Jones\u2019s Diary (2001)** - A hilarious and relatable story of self-discovery and love, starring Ren\u00e9e Zellweger.\n3. **My Big Fat Greek Wedding (2002)** - A charming and funny story about love and cultural differences.\n4. **Knocked Up (2007)** - A raunchy yet heartfelt comedy about unexpected pregnancy and relationships.\n5. **The Holiday (2006)** - A feel-good holiday rom-com with Cameron Diaz, Kate Winslet, Jude Law, and Jack Black.\n\nThese films offer a range of styles and tones, so there\u2019s something for everyone in the romantic comedy genre!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
